{"author":{"uri":{"label":"https://itunes.apple.com/us/reviews/id582290628"}, "name":{"label":"Hjk01996"}, "label":""}, "updated":{"label":"2026-03-25T15:07:50-07:00"}, "im:rating":{"label":"3"}, "im:version":{"label":"2.60"}, "id":{"label":"13886871178"}, "title":{"label":"Wish it wasn’t $25 to upgrade but it’s good for the most part"}, "content":{"label":"I really like this widget for its ability to be able to fit a lot of text in a medium sized widget for my home screen. That way I can see the most amount of things on my to do list all at once. I can’t justify paying $25 to upgrade to the “premium” features though, which sucks because they only give you one free font to use & it’s a very thin font. I have astigmatism & exotropia in my left eye so I would love to be able to use the bold font so it’d be easier to read. Also, you can’t make the widget transparent without paying the $25 to upgrade either. It also limits you as to how many tasks you can have & how many to do lists you can have without upgrading. All in all I could see paying $10 to upgrade but not $25. Even though it’s a one time payment — still not worth it in my eyes. Maybe if it had more features but honestly this is just a basic to do list widget.", "attributes":{"type":"text"}}, "link":{"attributes":{"rel":"related", "href":"https://itunes.apple.com/us/review?id=1585508533&type=Purple%20Software"}}, "im:voteSum":{"label":"0"}, "im:contentType":{"attributes":{"term":"Application", "label":"Application"}}, "im:voteCount":{"label":"0"}}, 
